---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import ImageText from '../../components/ImageText.astro';
import BookingCTA from '../../components/BookingCTA.astro';

const bookingUrl = 'https://go.mindbodyonline.com/book/widgets/appointments/view/8068777f5e/services';

const faqs = [
	{ q: 'What is Vojta Therapy?', a: 'It is a neurological rehabilitation method that uses reflex locomotion to activate automatic movement patterns within the body.' },
	{ q: 'Is it only for children?', a: 'No. While commonly used in infants and children, it is also effective for adults with neurological conditions.' },
	{ q: 'How is it different from other neurological therapies?', a: 'Vojta Therapy focuses on activating involuntary, reflex-driven movement patterns rather than relying solely on voluntary movement and task-based training.' },
	{ q: 'Will my child cry during treatment?', a: 'Some children may cry during sessions due to the effort involved. This is not typically due to pain, but rather the unfamiliar nature of the movement.' },
	{ q: 'How many sessions are needed?', a: 'This varies depending on the individual. A structured plan will be provided after the initial assessment.' },
	{ q: 'Do I need a referral?', a: 'No, you can book directly with us.' },
];
---
<Layout
	title="Vojta Therapy Clapham | Neurological Movement & Rehab Therapy"
	description="Vojta Therapy in Clapham to improve movement, posture, and neurological function. Specialist rehab for children and adults with neurological conditions."
>
	<PageHero title="in South West London" highlight="Vojta Therapy" breadcrumb="Vojta Therapy" />

	<div class="service-intro">
	<ImageText eyebrow="Our approach" heading="Activating innate" highlight="movement patterns" image="/vojta-therapy/movement-patterns.jpg" imageAlt="Vojta Therapy session at Balance">
		<p>Movement problems linked to the nervous system can affect how the body develops, adapts, and functions day to day.</p>
		<p>Vojta Therapy is a specialised neurological treatment that works by activating innate movement patterns within the central nervous system. Rather than relying on voluntary effort alone, it stimulates automatic responses that underpin posture, coordination, and mobility.</p>
		<p>At Balance, we take a structured and evidence-led approach to neurological rehabilitation. From your first session, we assess how movement is organised and controlled, then build a plan that supports both immediate function and long-term development.</p>
		<p>Whether for a child with developmental concerns or an adult recovering from neurological injury, the focus is the same: improving how the body moves at a fundamental level.</p>
		<p><a href={bookingUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-primary">Book Now</a></p>
	</ImageText>
	</div>

	<section class="text-grid">
		<div class="text-grid-inner">
			<div class="image-text-content text-grid-cell">
				<div class="eyebrow">Symptoms</div>
				<h2>When to consider <span class="highlight">Vojta Therapy</span></h2>
				<p>Vojta Therapy can be particularly effective where movement is limited by neurological inhibition.</p>
				<p>You may benefit if you or your child are experiencing:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Delays in motor development such as rolling, crawling, or walking</li>
					<li>Difficulties with coordination, posture, or muscle tone</li>
					<li>Asymmetrical movement or a preference for one side</li>
					<li>Spasticity or stiffness affecting fluid movement</li>
					<li>Neurological conditions such as cerebral palsy</li>
					<li>Movement limitations following stroke or brain injury</li>
				</ul>
				<p>If movement patterns are not developing or functioning as expected, early assessment is important.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="image-text-content text-grid-cell text-grid-cell--treatment">
				<div class="eyebrow">Treatment</div>
				<h2>How we <span class="highlight">work</span></h2>
				<p>Vojta Therapy is based on activating specific zones of the body to trigger automatic movement responses.</p>
				<p>Your treatment may include:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Targeted stimulation of reflex points to activate global movement patterns</li>
					<li>Positioning to support postural control and alignment</li>
					<li>Guidance for home-based therapy where appropriate</li>
					<li>Ongoing reassessment of movement quality and control</li>
				</ul>
				<p>The aim is to access and reinforce fundamental patterns such as turning, creeping, and postural stabilisation, building a foundation for more complex movement.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="text-grid text-grid--light">
		<div class="text-grid-inner">
			<div class="image-text-content text-grid-cell">
				<div class="eyebrow">Outcomes</div>
				<h2>How we measure <span class="highlight">your progress</span></h2>
				<p>Progress in neurological rehabilitation is tracked carefully over time.</p>
				<p>From your first session, we assess:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Movement patterns and symmetry</li>
					<li>Postural control</li>
					<li>Muscle tone and coordination</li>
					<li>Functional ability relative to milestones, age or condition</li>
				</ul>
				<p>As therapy progresses, we monitor changes in how movement is organised and controlled. The goal is improved automatic control of movement, not just temporary change.</p>
				<p><a href="/outcomes" class="section-link">Read More About Outcome Measures &rarr;</a></p>
			</div>
			<div class="image-text-content text-grid-cell text-grid-cell--treatment">
				<div class="eyebrow">Our patients</div>
				<h2>Who we <span class="highlight">help</span></h2>
				<p>We support a wide range of patients across South West London:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Infants and children with developmental delays or neurological conditions</li>
					<li>Children with cerebral palsy or motor control disorders</li>
					<li>Adults recovering from stroke or neurological injury</li>
					<li>Individuals with complex movement disorders not responding to traditional therapy</li>
				</ul>
				<p>We also work closely with families, providing guidance and support throughout the rehabilitation process.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<ImageText reverse altBg eyebrow="Our team" heading="Our clinical" highlight="specialist" image="/vojta-therapy/jose-portrait.jpg" imageAlt="Dr Jose Sanz Mengibar">
		<p>Our Vojta Therapy service is led by <strong>Dr Jose Sanz Mengibar</strong>, Consultant Neurological Physiotherapist and certified Vojta Therapist.</p>
		<p>With over 20 years of clinical and research experience and a PhD in the field, Dr Jose has a deep understanding of neurological movement disorders. His approach focuses on identifying the specific inputs required to trigger effective motor responses, delivering highly individualised care for both children and adults.</p>
		<p><a href="/meet-the-team" class="section-link">Read More About Jose &rarr;</a></p>
		<p><strong>Integrated care.</strong> Where appropriate, we work closely with the wider Balance team. This may include joint sessions with physiotherapists and other specialists, ensuring your treatment carries through into everyday movement and function.</p>
		<p><a href="/meet-the-team" class="section-link">Meet The Team &rarr;</a></p>
	</ImageText>

	<section class="text-grid text-grid--light">
		<div class="text-grid-inner">
			<div class="image-text-content text-grid-cell">
				<div class="eyebrow">Fees</div>
				<h2>Pricing and <span class="highlight">insurance</span></h2>
				<p>We offer a transparent fee structure that reflects our level of clinical expertise.</p>
				<p><a href="/pricing#neurological-rehabilitation" class="section-link">Pricing Information &rarr;</a></p>
			</div>
			<div class="text-grid-cell">
				<div class="testimonial-card">
					<p>Without Jose's therapy, input and expertise, my daughter would not have the mobility she has today. Jose has guided us as a family in the best interest of our daughter. My daughter has been seeing Jose for over 14 years and we would not trust anyone else regarding our daughter's therapy and well-being. His empathy towards us as a family is beyond amazing.</p>
					<div class="testimonial-author">
						<div class="testimonial-avatar">
							<img src="/vojta-therapy/testimonial-avatar.jpg" alt="Vojta Therapy testimonial" />
						</div>
						<div>
							<h4>Vojta Therapy patient family</h4>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="faq-section faq-section--alt">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="section-header"><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2></div>
			<div class="faq-list">
				{faqs.map((item) => (
					<details class="faq-item">
						<summary>{item.q}</summary>
						<div class="answer">{item.a}</div>
					</details>
				))}
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<BookingCTA />
</Layout>
